			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Job Description</strong></p>
<p>
The lead DBA will take responsibility of support and management of the enterprise-wide PostgreSQL Databases in live, development and test environments.</p>
<p>
The lead DBA will work closely with the system engineers, Service desk, and software engineering, on database related projects, interfaces and support tickets.</p>
<p>
The successful incumbent will manage and maintain backup and recovery plans, implement and maintain database security, perform capacity planning, performance optimization, and will be part of a follow the sun service support function as well to an call rotation support.</p>
<p>
<strong>Primary duties and responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience at an eCommerce provider in a technical lead capacity.</li>
<li>
Administration of production PostgreSQL and MySQL databases in high-availability environment deployed across multiple datacenters.</li>
<li>
Provide system engineering, administration, installation, configuration management, performance tuning and capacity planning.</li>
<li>
Ensuring overall performance, availability and reliability of all live databases in conformance with service level agreements (SLA) and best practices.</li>
<li>
Development and document standards, policies and procedures for Database operations</li>
<li>
Lead collaboration with Development group to identify software bottlenecks and optimizations</li>
<li>
Drive System Administration group to identify hardware bottlenecks and to establish server configurations.</li>
<li>
Responsibility for managing/supporting data within the databases itself including data analysis, reporting or investigation, mitigation, data cleansing.</li>
<li>
Assist in the mentoring and coaching of less senior level database team members</li>
<li>
Have worked in 24 x 7 environments and willingness to be part of OnCall</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Desired skills</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Deep expertise in PostgreSQL and MySQL&ndash; Certification in a major DB a plus.</li>
<li>
Effective problem-solving skills in a high pressure, demanding environment, specifically the ability to assess situations, evaluate options, make decisions, draw conclusions, and exercise judgment.</li>
<li>
Experience in being part of an on call rotation providing 24x7 support for production database issues</li>
<li>
Experience in planning and executing database server installations, database migration, upgrades, patches</li>
<li>
Experience in managing and maintaining backup and recovery plans, database security, capacity planning, performance tuning</li>
<li>
Ability to anticipate potential problems, determine and implement solutions.</li>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science, MIS, Engineering, (any type) or a related field</li>
<li>
Database architecture and design skills</li>
<li>
Team players who can both lead and work collaboratively in a fast-paced environment.</li>
<li>
Excellent organizational, communication, and interpersonal skills.</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
