			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Job Purpose</strong></p>
<p>
Manage all aspects of the commercial relationship with assigned clients; ensure they make best possible use of the Venda platform (owning the business case); helping customers to realise their growth and expansion targets.</p>
<p>
<strong>Principal Job Objectives</strong></p>
<p>
1. Manage the commercial client relationship, as the principal client contact, e.g.:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Ensure customers always have confidence in Venda, by representing Venda in a professional manner, and carefully managing customer expectations.</li>
<li>
Maintain knowledge of your clients&rsquo; contractual status, flagging key notice periods for contract renewal. RAG Dashboard /Highlights</li>
<li>
Maintain an &lsquo;overall&rsquo; view of assigned clients, including any ongoing projects, enhancements, support issues or disputes that may originate or be the responsibility of other internal Venda teams. Confluence Roadmap</li>
<li>
Be aware of all contacts between Venda and assigned clients, taking a proactive role wherever required to facilitate communication or advice to the client or internal team. Code upgrades communication and Planned Maintenance</li>
<li>
Maintain regular communication with all clients, on both a Face-to-face, written and verbal basis, being ready to reactively and proactively engage or initiate any request that may come about. F2F Quarterly Profit Clinics; Account Reviews; Conference Calls</li>
<li>
Communicate directly with your clients where you foresee strain in the client relationship, for instance following up on a service incident, ongoing support issue or contract renewal, etc. Act as the internal voice of the customer to escalate and mitigate risks and issues</li>
<li>
Escalate any issues outside of your control at the earliest opportunity. Drive a culture of accountability within the organisation OPS, Golive sessions, sessions with support and SDM</li>
</ul>
<p>
2. Consult with the client to leverage the best of the Venda solution to optimise their site&rsquo;s performance, e.g.:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Maintain a view of client commercial performance, understanding the client&rsquo;s perception of this and their targets/ KPI&rsquo;s.&nbsp; Report regularly on these client targets and objectives to all stakeholders in agreed format Dashboard, Highlights, TLM</li>
<li>
Take the lead on commercial discussions in relation to client enhancements &ndash; engage with relevant teams for specific advice/guidance, making proactive suggestions and offering viable solutions to customers such that they can meet their targets as cost effectively as possible. Utilise both Solution Engineering and TPE as a means of establishing solution and business case respectively.</li>
<li>
Be aware of client&rsquo;s knowledge gaps around the platform, VCP and templates &ndash; proactively suggesting the most appropriate solutions for any knowledge gaps Create and utilise&nbsp; training resource(s) to promote Venda services, functionality and capability.</li>
<li>
Provide ongoing Ecommerce analysis, at a suitable level to the role, using relevant analytical tools to inform and further consult with clients on site performance and optimisation. Google Analytics, Webtrends, Industry media/articles.</li>
<li>
Proactively seek information on upcoming Venda code updates to understand the ongoing improvement and development of the Venda solution. Set expectations with clients in relation to code upgrades, offering commercial guidance and support where necessary (in terms of implications for roadmap).</li>
<li>
Ensure clients are aware of any upcoming developments on the Venda platform and take full advantage of any feature that would help them to meet their targets.</li>
<li>
Work closely with the client and internal teams to precisely gather enhancement scope/high level business requirements, such that high margin is achieved through effective delivery Functionality Requirements Documentation</li>
<li>
Ensure clients make full use of existing platform functionality, with a minimal level of platform development. Standard Functionality Checklist</li>
<li>
Track client&rsquo;s marketing and sales activities, providing forecast and capacity management advice to clients and internal Venda stakeholders. Christmas forecasts and any marketing initiated peaks</li>
</ul>
<p>
3. Deliver service revenue to agreed targets, e.g.:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Provide clients with timely, consistent and clear quotes.</li>
<li>
Control and monitor the chargeable and non-chargeable work that is being completed for assigned clients.</li>
<li>
Wherever an opportunity exists, within the Venda charging framework, increase Venda service revenues.</li>
<li>
Maintain a clear view of the upcoming revenue pipeline for your assigned clients.</li>
</ul>
<p>
4. Contribute to the Account Management team, e.g.:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Help ensure the working environment is professional, positive and enjoyable place to work.</li>
<li>
Work with management to produce an &ldquo;excellent&rdquo; team.</li>
<li>
Train and mentor team mates &ndash; taking a full part in any meetings or training and development sessions</li>
<li>
Challenge the status quo and enhance processes and documentation wherever you see an opportunity.</li>
<li>
Look for opportunities to add increased value to Commercial teams/activities.</li>
<li>
Perform other duties, as required, to assist in managing and delivering world class Convergent-Commerce solutions to our clients.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Knowledge, Experience &amp; Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Have Commercial/Account Management experience, gained in the eCommerce / SaaS sector.</li>
<li>
Successfully managed clients through the full client lifecycle, from initial on-boarding through to successful maturity and growth.</li>
<li>
Successfully delivered incremental service revenues with high levels of client retention and renewal of service.</li>
<li>
A track record of successfully managing difficult and demanding clients, while facilitating between the client and the company during periods of stress and conflict.</li>
<li>
Created and delivered effective, pragmatic, timely and cost-effective solutions to business issues and user requirements that leverage the Venda&rsquo;s solution to meet the client&rsquo;s needs.</li>
<li>
Exposure to project-based development useful.</li>
<li>
Experienced in delivering training to professionals and maintaining interest in a training program.</li>
<li>
Educated to degree level or equivalent.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Skills</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
The ability to build professional relationships with clients across different vertical markets and backgrounds, showing empathy and understanding toward contacts with varying outlooks and personalities.</li>
<li>
Proven, and demonstrable, customer management ability: quick to comprehend requirements, clear in explanation of solutions, and extremely capable in steering and managing customer expectations through difficult situations.</li>
<li>
Confident and self-assured, displaying an air of gravitas and professionalism in all client dealings, comfortable with presenting and influencing at all levels.</li>
<li>
Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal, and able to communicate to all levels in the organisation.</li>
<li>
Extremely flexible and adept at managing change and conflicting priorities, against a backdrop of a dynamic entrepreneurial organisation.</li>
<li>
Able to operate as a team player.</li>
<li>
Self-motivated and can work at a senior level with minimal supervision.</li>
<li>
Target driven with the ability to easily understand what is required to meet the key indicators for your position and the proven ability to consistently meet agreed performance targets.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Direct Reports</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
None</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
