			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Role</strong></p>
<p>
The position of QA Analyst will be to support the continuing success and growth of the Venda by ensuring quality standards are met during the delivery of changes to the Venda Ecommerce Platform.&nbsp; The role will be responsible for conducting testing of code releases, patches and projects, and helping the QA team continuously improve the service it provides to internal/external customers.&nbsp; The individual will be expected to maintain high quality standards across all aspects of the role including automated test scripts creation/maintenance setting an example to team members and colleagues.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Create test plans and test cases from requirement specifications and user stories.</li>
<li>
Understand development requirements and take responsibility for testing to ensure requirements and quality standards are met.</li>
<li>
Be proactive in working with developers, and other staff, to ensure efficient progress of issues.</li>
<li>
Provide test result reports for stakeholders and departments, on time.</li>
<li>
Execution of functional, regression and release (patch) testing for the core platform applications.</li>
<li>
To write, modify and maintain test plans, test scripts, and test data according to business demands.</li>
<li>
Track defects and fixes within internal and external projects.</li>
<li>
Contribute testing knowledge and expertise to all phases of the development lifecycle.</li>
<li>
Analysing and interpreting technical data/reports generated by automated testing tools.</li>
<li>
Executing and generating reports for both manual and automated testing tools, including analysis of these reports.</li>
<li>
Provide weekly reporting on personal progress and achievements against objectives.</li>
<li>
Ensure continuous learning and improvement throughout the performing of the role.</li>
<li>
Contribute to project, team, and department meetings.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Required Skills and Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience of using automated testing tools such as Selenium, Cucumber, or TestNG testing tools combined with Ruby programming language</li>
<li>
Excellent technical aptitude and knowledge of QA methodologies, processes and roles.</li>
<li>
Experience communicating with technical and development teams.</li>
<li>
Ability to use basic Linux command lines; experience desirable.</li>
<li>
Experience with full software development lifecycle.</li>
<li>
Commercial experience of using test case management, defect tracking &amp; bug management tools such as JIRA.</li>
<li>
Significant experience of testing high volume, heavy transactional e-commerce websites or systems.</li>
<li>
Knowledge in capacity planning and project estimation.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Personal Qualities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Excellent attention to detail and a passion for ensuring quality.</li>
<li>
Enthusiasm for experimenting with new techniques to help improve and advance processes.</li>
<li>
Ability to communicate orally and in writing to all levels of staff in a clear, concise and convincing manner</li>
<li>
Able to multitask and work under pressure and deadlines.</li>
<li>
Ability to question established procedures and suggest improvement and alternatives.</li>
<li>
Highly motivated, proactive and able to work on own initiative.</li>
<li>
Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and able to accept rapidly changing business priorities.</li>
<li>
A willingness to be part of a team, and able to accept individual and collective responsibility.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
