			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>The Role</strong></p>
<p>
The role requires the strong application of Quality Assurance practices for the Venda Technology Group team. The role will involve managing the existing QA team, leading the expansion and scalability of the team through the roll-out of automated testing, implementing best practice and performance monitoring. Working alongside the development teams you will be tasked with further developing the test and QA strategy. This will be a broad ranging position, critical to the overall business strategy and with significant focus in driving the automated testing procedures forward.&nbsp; We are looking for a dedicated, self-motivated, driven and experienced individual with very strong experience in QA methodologies, Agile project involvement and automation testing techniques expertise.</p>
<p>
<strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Responsible for complex automation and coverage techniques. Must be considered an expert within this field.</li>
<li>
Own all aspects of running and managing an Automated Managed Test Service.</li>
<li>
Reviews test scripts to ensure adherence to company&#39;s standards.</li>
<li>
Plans &amp; executes work that includes complex testing of high risk application areas.</li>
<li>
Improves upon QA approaches and processes.</li>
<li>
Applies significant experience from various SDLC models &amp; provides training to co-workers.</li>
<li>
Able to suggest and implement improvements to framework/ utilities.</li>
<li>
Advanced understanding of test frameworks.</li>
<li>
Capable of writing advanced test utilities if necessary.</li>
<li>
Works independently, requires no supervision for work tasks and minimal guidance for development of skills and career.</li>
<li>
Acts as a role model for other QA Engineers.</li>
<li>
Provides technical QA leadership to team members.</li>
<li>
Responsible for the supervision, guidance &amp; mentoring of other QA engineers.</li>
<li>
Responsible for the QA resource management optimizing resource based on business priority.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Key Working Relationships</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Working with other teams as part of a software project team to deliver quality software to deadlines.</li>
<li>
Demonstrate an ability to work closely with developers and build cross discipline relationships.</li>
<li>
Work with developers and QA staff to assist in writing test plans, test cases, and acceptance tests to help ensure quality processes.</li>
<li>
Liaise with project managers in the scheduling of pre-development quality assurance and post-development test execution.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Essential Technical Skills</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Strong Experience in the creation and maintenance of automated test scripts with a specific Selenium and Ruby expertise.</li>
<li>
Background in functional testing with the ability to plan, design, script and execute automation/manual test cases.</li>
<li>
Broad experience of the various models of the SDLC, with a high priority focus on Agile Software Delivery.</li>
<li>
Familiar with different types of testing frameworks; data driven and keyword driven.</li>
<li>
Educated to degree level in a science or technology related field.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Essential Soft Skills</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Really good communication skills (written, oral, presentations).</li>
<li>
Ability to bridge gaps and communicate effectively between cross functional teams.</li>
<li>
Excellent management and communication skills.</li>
<li>
Able to manage workload effectively.</li>
<li>
Self-motivating, adaptable and flexible.</li>
<li>
Able to work in a rapid development environment with flexible requirements.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Desirable Skills</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience of working in a Software As a Service or service delivery environment.</li>
<li>
Previous experience of the e-commerce industry.</li>
<li>
Awareness of the different types of testing frameworks; data driven and keyword driven.</li>
<li>
Awareness of object oriented programming concepts and how they should be used in test- framework architecture.</li>
<li>
Experience of SQL and database testing.</li>
<li>
ISEB Foundation Certificate in Software Testing.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Knowledge, Experience &amp; Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Substantial experience creating automated user acceptance tests for web sites.</li>
<li>
Proactive work ethic with the ability to deliver results and meet challenging deadlines in a really fast-paced delivery environment.</li>
<li>
Proven experience developing/improving QA processes, increasing delivery efficiency and developing direct reports.</li>
<li>
Experience with customer centric industries and mission critical quality software standards.</li>
<li>
Significant experience in applying automated testing tools to number of successful software projects.</li>
<li>
An understanding of the strengths and limitations of specific testing tools.</li>
</ul>
